This paper discusses the normative implications of machine learning models on social systems, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the potential disparate impact on minority and marginalized groups, which is a common concern in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches on the need for developing tools to identify and interpret harms introduced by models, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the objectives of social equity and distributive justice, which is a topic in social informatics (cs.SI).
